      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import librosa\n",
        "import warnings\n",
        "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Optimized imports\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, VotingClassifier\n",
        "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, cross_val_score, StratifiedKFold\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, RobustScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, roc_auc_score, f1_score\n",
        "from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectFromModel\n",
        "from xgboost import XGBClassifier\n",
        "from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier\n",
        "import joblib\n",
        "import time\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"üöÄ ULTRA-EFFICIENT PARKINSON'S DETECTOR\")\n",
        "print(\"========================================\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. OPTIMIZED DATA LOADING WITH CACHING\n",
        "@joblib.Memory(location='./cache', verbose=0).cache\n",
        "def load_optimized_data():\n",
        "    \"\"\"Ultra-efficient data loading with caching\"\"\"\n",
        "    print(\"üì• Loading dataset...\")\n",
        "    !wget -q -O parkinsons.data https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/parkinsons/parkinsons.data\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Memory-optimized loading\n",
        "    data = pd.read_csv('parkinsons.data')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Optimize data types\n",
        "    for col in data.columns:\n",
        "        if data[col].dtype == 'float64':\n",
        "            data[col] = data[col].astype(np.float32)\n",
        "        elif data[col].dtype == 'int64':\n",
        "            data[col] = data[col].astype(np.int8)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return data\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. ADVANCED FEATURE ENGINEERING\n",
        "def create_advanced_features(X):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Create medically relevant feature interactions\"\"\"\n",
        "    X_engineered = X.copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Medical ratio features (proven to be important)\n",
        "    if all(col in X.columns for col in ['MDVP:Fhi(Hz)', 'MDVP:Flo(Hz)']):\n",
        "        X_engineered['pitch_variability_ratio'] = (X['MDVP:Fhi(Hz)'] - X['MDVP:Flo(Hz)']) / X['MDVP:Fo(Hz)']\n",
        "\n",
        "    if all(col in X.columns for col in ['MDVP:Jitter(%)', 'MDVP:Shimmer']):\n",
        "        X_engineered['perturbation_index'] = X['MDVP:Jitter(%)'] * X['MDVP:Shimmer']\n",
        "        X_engineered['stability_score'] = 1 / (X['MDVP:Jitter(%)'] + X['MDVP:Shimmer'] + 1e-8)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Non-linear combinations\n",
        "    if 'HNR' in X.columns:\n",
        "        X_engineered['hnr_log'] = np.log1p(X['HNR'])\n",
        "        X_engineered['voice_quality'] = X['HNR'] / (X['MDVP:Jitter(%)'] + 1e-8)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Statistical aggregates\n",
        "    X_engineered['feature_complexity'] = X.std(axis=1) / (X.mean(axis=1) + 1e-8)\n",
        "    X_engineered['feature_range'] = X.max(axis=1) - X.min(axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return X_engineered\n",
        "\n",
        "# Helper function to sanitize feature names\n",
        "def sanitize_feature_names(df):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Sanitize feature names to be compatible with LightGBM and other models.\"\"\"\n",
        "    new_columns = []\n",
        "    for col in df.columns:\n",
        "        # Replace special characters with underscores and remove parentheses/brackets\n",
        "        new_col = col.replace(':', '_').replace('(', '').replace(')', '').replace('%', 'percent').replace('[', '').replace(']', '').replace('<', '_lt_').replace('>', '_gt_').replace(',', '_').replace(' ', '_')\n",
        "        new_columns.append(new_col)\n",
        "    df.columns = new_columns\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. OPTIMAL FEATURE SELECTION\n",
        "def select_optimal_features(X, y, n_features=18):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Select most predictive features using ensemble importance\"\"\"\n",
        "    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Ensemble feature selection\n",
        "    selectors = [\n",
        "        XGBClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42),\n",
        "        LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42),\n",
        "        ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    feature_scores = pd.DataFrame({'feature': X.columns})\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i, selector in enumerate(selectors):\n",
        "        selector.fit(X, y)\n",
        "        feature_scores[f'score_{i}'] = selector.feature_importances_\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Weighted ensemble scoring\n",
        "    feature_scores['ensemble_score'] = (\n",
        "        feature_scores['score_0'] * 0.4 +\n",
        "        feature_scores['score_1'] * 0.4 +\n",
        "        feature_scores['score_2'] * 0.2\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    selected_features = feature_scores.nlargest(n_features, 'ensemble_score')['feature'].tolist()\n",
        "    print(f\"üéØ Selected {len(selected_features)} optimal features\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return selected_features\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. ADVANCED ENSEMBLE MODEL\n",
        "def create_advanced_ensemble():\n",
        "    \"\"\"Create optimized ensemble with tuned hyperparameters\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Highly optimized XGBoost\n",
        "    xgb = XGBClassifier(\n",
        "        n_estimators=200,\n",
        "        max_depth=8,\n",
        "        learning_rate=0.1,\n",
        "        subsample=0.85,\n",
        "        colsample_bytree=0.85,\n",
        "        reg_alpha=0.1,\n",
        "        reg_lambda=0.1,\n",
        "        gamma=0.1,\n",
        "        random_state=42,\n",
        "        n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "        eval_metric='logloss'\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Optimized LightGBM\n",
        "    lgb = LGBMClassifier(\n",
        "        n_estimators=180,\n",
        "        max_depth=7,\n",
        "        learning_rate=0.1,\n",
        "        num_leaves=35,\n",
        "        subsample=0.85,\n",
        "        colsample_bytree=0.85,\n",
        "        reg_alpha=0.1,\n",
        "        reg_lambda=0.1,\n",
        "        random_state=42,\n",
        "        n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "        verbosity=-1\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Enhanced Random Forest\n",
        "    rf = RandomForestClassifier(\n",
        "        n_estimators=200,\n",
        "        max_depth=15,\n",
        "        min_samples_split=3,\n",
        "        min_samples_leaf=1,\n",
        "        max_features='sqrt',\n",
        "        bootstrap=True,\n",
        "        random_state=42,\n",
        "        n_jobs=-1\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    # SVM for diversity (kernel approximation for speed)\n",
        "    svm = SVC(\n",
        "        C=1.0,\n",
        "        kernel='rbf',\n",
        "        gamma='scale',\n",
        "        probability=True,\n",
        "        random_state=42,\n",
        "        cache_size=1000\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Weighted ensemble based on expected performance\n",
        "    ensemble = VotingClassifier(\n",
        "        estimators=[\n",
        "            ('xgb', xgb),\n",
        "            ('lgb', lgb),\n",
        "            ('rf', rf),\n",
        "            # ('svm', svm)  # Optional: adds diversity but increases computation\n",
        "        ],\n",
        "        voting='soft',\n",
        "        weights=[4, 4, 3],  # Weighted by expected performance\n",
        "        n_jobs=-1\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    return ensemble\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. ULTRA-EFFICIENT VOICE PROCESSOR\n",
        "class UltraVoiceProcessor:\n",
        "    \"\"\"Highly optimized voice feature extraction\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __init__(self, sr=22050, duration=2.5):\n",
        "        self.sr = sr\n",
        "        self.duration = duration\n",
        "        self.feature_cache = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "    def extract_ultra_features(self, audio_path):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Extract comprehensive features with medical relevance\"\"\"\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            # Cache for repeated processing\n",
        "            cache_key = hash(audio_path)\n",
        "            if cache_key in self.feature_cache:\n",
        "                return self.feature_cache[cache_key]\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Load with optimized parameters\n",
        "            y, sr = librosa.load(audio_path, sr=self.sr, duration=self.duration, mono=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "            features = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "            # 1. PITCH ANALYSIS (Most important)\n",
        "            pitch_features = self._extract_pitch_analysis(y)\n",
        "            features.update(pitch_features)\n",
        "\n",
        "            # 2. PERTURBATION MEASURES\n",
        "            perturbation_features = self._extract_perturbation_measures(y, pitch_features.get('f0_mean', 120))\n",
        "            features.update(perturbation_features)\n",
        "\n",
        "            # 3. SPECTRAL ANALYSIS\n",
        "            spectral_features = self._extract_spectral_analysis(y)\n",
        "            features.update(spectral_features)\n",
        "\n",
        "            # 4. VOICE QUALITY METRICS\n",
        "            quality_features = self._extract_voice_quality(y)\n",
        "            features.update(quality_features)\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Convert to optimized array\n",
        "            feature_array = self._features_to_optimized_array(features)\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Cache results\n",
        "            self.feature_cache[cache_key] = feature_array\n",
        "\n",
        "            return feature_array\n",
        "\n",
        "        except Exception as e:\n",
        "            print(f\"‚ùå Processing error: {e}\")\n",
        "            return np.zeros(25, dtype=np.float32)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _extract_pitch_analysis(self, y):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Comprehensive pitch analysis\"\"\"\n",
        "        f0, voiced_flag, _ = librosa.pyin(\n",
        "            y, fmin=50, fmax=300, sr=self.sr,\n",
        "            frame_length=2048, hop_length=512, fill_na=0.0\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "        voiced_f0 = f0[voiced_flag & (f0 > 0)]\n",
        "\n",
        "        if len(voiced_f0) > 15:\n",
        "            return {\n",
        "                'f0_mean': np.mean(voiced_f0),\n",
        "                'f0_std': np.std(voiced_f0),\n",
        "                'f0_coeff_var': np.std(voiced_f0) / (np.mean(voiced_f0) + 1e-8),\n",
        "                'f0_range': np.ptp(voiced_f0),\n",
        "                'f0_median': np.median(voiced_f0),\n",
        "                'f0_iqr': np.percentile(voiced_f0, 75) - np.percentile(voiced_f0, 25),\n",
        "                'voicing_rate': np.mean(voiced_flag)\n",
        "            }\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            # Return medically reasonable defaults\n",
        "            return {\n",
        "                'f0_mean': 120.0, 'f0_std': 25.0, 'f0_coeff_var': 0.2,\n",
        "                'f0_range': 80.0, 'f0_median': 120.0, 'f0_iqr': 30.0,\n",
        "                'voicing_rate': 0.75\n",
        "            }\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _extract_perturbation_measures(self, y, f0_mean):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Advanced jitter and shimmer analysis\"\"\"\n",
        "        frame_length, hop_length = 2048, 512\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Jitter calculation from pitch\n",
        "        f0 = librosa.pyin(y, fmin=50, fmax=300, fill_na=0.0)[0]\n",
        "        f0 = f0[f0 > 0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        if len(f0) > 10:\n",
        "            jitter_absolute = np.mean(np.abs(np.diff(f0)))\n",
        "            jitter_relative = jitter_absolute / (np.mean(f0) + 1e-8)\n",
        "            jitter_rap = np.mean(np.abs(f0[2:] - 2*f0[1:-1] + f0[:-2])) / (np.mean(f0) + 1e-8)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            jitter_absolute, jitter_relative, jitter_rap = 0.0001, 0.0008, 0.0005\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Shimmer from amplitude envelope\n",
        "        rms = librosa.feature.rms(y=y, frame_length=frame_length, hop_length=hop_length)[0]\n",
        "        if len(rms) > 10:\n",
        "            shimmer_absolute = np.mean(np.abs(np.diff(rms)))\n",
        "            shimmer_relative = shimmer_absolute / (np.mean(rms) + 1e-8)\n",
        "            shimmer_apq3 = np.mean([np.std(rms[i:i+3]) for i in range(len(rms)-2)]) / (np.mean(rms) + 1e-8)\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            shimmer_absolute, shimmer_relative, shimmer_apq3 = 0.001, 0.02, 0.015\n",
        "\n",
        "        return {\n",
        "            'jitter_abs': jitter_absolute,\n",
        "            'jitter_percent': jitter_relative * 100,\n",
        "            'jitter_rap': jitter_rap,\n",
        "            'shimmer_abs': shimmer_absolute,\n",
        "            'shimmer_percent': shimmer_relative * 100,\n",
        "            'shimmer_apq3': shimmer_apq3\n",
        "        }\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _extract_spectral_analysis(self, y):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Comprehensive spectral analysis\"\"\"\n",
        "        # MFCCs (most important spectral features)\n",
        "        mfccs = librosa.feature.mfcc(y=y, sr=self.sr, n_mfcc=13, n_fft=2048, hop_length=512)\n",
        "        mfcc_means = [np.mean(mfccs[i]) for i in range(min(8, mfccs.shape[0]))]\n",
        "        mfcc_stds = [np.std(mfccs[i]) for i in range(min(5, mfccs.shape[0]))]\n",
        "\n",
        "        mfcc_features = {}\n",
        "        for i, mean_val in enumerate(mfcc_means):\n",
        "            mfcc_features[f'mfcc{i+1}_mean'] = mean_val\n",
        "        for i, std_val in enumerate(mfcc_stds):\n",
        "            mfcc_features[f'mfcc{i+1}_std'] = std_val\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Additional spectral features\n",
        "        spectral_centroid = librosa.feature.spectral_centroid(y=y, sr=self.sr)\n",
        "        spectral_rolloff = librosa.feature.spectral_rolloff(y=y, sr=self.sr)\n",
        "        spectral_bandwidth = librosa.feature.spectral_bandwidth(y=y, sr=self.sr)\n",
        "\n",
        "        mfcc_features.update({\n",
        "            'spectral_centroid': np.mean(spectral_centroid),\n",
        "            'spectral_rolloff': np.mean(spectral_rolloff),\n",
        "            'spectral_bandwidth': np.mean(spectral_bandwidth),\n",
        "            'spectral_flatness': np.mean(librosa.feature.spectral_flatness(y=y))\n",
        "        })\n",
        "\n",
        "        return mfcc_features\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _extract_voice_quality(self, y):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Voice quality and non-linear measures\"\"\"\n",
        "        # Harmonics-to-Noise Ratio\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            y_harmonic = librosa.effects.harmonic(y, margin=8)\n",
        "            y_noise = y - y_harmonic\n",
        "            hnr = np.sqrt(np.mean(y_harmonic**2)) / (np.sqrt(np.mean(y_noise**2)) + 1e-8)\n",
        "            hnr = min(hnr, 25.0)\n",
        "        except:\n",
        "            hnr = 15.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Non-linear dynamics approximations\n",
        "        return {\n",
        "            'hnr': hnr,\n",
        "            'rpde': 0.55,  # Placeholder - would require complex calculation\n",
        "            'dfa': 0.65,   # Placeholder\n",
        "            'ppe': 0.095,  # Placeholder\n",
        "            'd2': 0.75,    # Placeholder\n",
        "            'spread1': 2.1,\n",
        "            'spread2': 0.18\n",
        "        }\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _features_to_optimized_array(self, features_dict):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Convert to optimized feature array\"\"\"\n",
        "        feature_order = [\n",
        "            'f0_mean', 'f0_std', 'f0_coeff_var', 'f0_range', 'f0_median', 'f0_iqr',\n",
        "            'voicing_rate', 'jitter_abs', 'jitter_percent', 'jitter_rap',\n",
        "            'shimmer_abs', 'shimmer_percent', 'shimmer_apq3', 'hnr',\n",
        "            'mfcc1_mean', 'mfcc2_mean', 'mfcc3_mean', 'mfcc4_mean', 'mfcc5_mean',\n",
        "            'mfcc1_std', 'mfcc2_std', 'spectral_centroid', 'spectral_rolloff',\n",
        "            'spectral_bandwidth', 'spectral_flatness'\n",
        "        ]\n",
        "\n",
        "        return np.array([features_dict.get(key, 0.0) for key in feature_order], dtype=np.float32)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 6. ADVANCED TRAINING PIPELINE\n",
        "def run_advanced_pipeline():\n",
        "    \"\"\"Complete optimized training pipeline\"\"\"\n",
        "    start_time = time.time()\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(\"üéØ Starting advanced training pipeline...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Load data\n",
        "    data = load_optimized_data()\n",
        "    print(f\"üìä Dataset: {data.shape[0]} samples, {data.shape[1]} features\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Prepare features\n",
        "    X = data.drop(['name', 'status'], axis=1)\n",
        "    y = data['status']\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Advanced feature engineering\n",
        "    print(\"üîß Engineering advanced features...\")\n",
        "    X_engineered = create_advanced_features(X)\n",
        "    # Sanitize feature names for LightGBM compatibility\n",
        "    X_engineered = sanitize_feature_names(X_engineered)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Optimal feature selection\n",
        "    print(\"üéØ Selecting optimal features...\")\n",
        "    optimal_features = select_optimal_features(X_engineered, y, n_features=20)\n",
        "    X_optimal = X_engineered[optimal_features]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Split with stratification\n",
        "    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
        "        X_optimal, y, test_size=0.15, random_state=42, stratify=y\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Advanced scaling\n",
        "    scaler = RobustScaler()  # More robust to outliers\n",
        "    X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
        "    X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Train advanced ensemble\n",
        "    print(\"ü§ñ Training advanced ensemble...\")\n",
        "    model = create_advanced_ensemble()\n",
        "    model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "    training_time = time.time() - start_time\n",
        "\n",
        "    # COMPREHENSIVE EVALUATION\n",
        "    print(\"üìä Comprehensive evaluation...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Cross-validation\n",
        "    cv = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)\n",
        "    cv_scores = cross_val_score(model, X_train_scaled, y_train, cv=cv, scoring='accuracy', n_jobs=-1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Predictions\n",
        "    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
        "    y_pred_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Multiple metrics\n",
        "    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "    auc_score = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_proba)\n",
        "    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(f\"‚è±Ô∏è  Training time: {training_time:.2f}s\")\n",
        "    print(f\"üìä 5-Fold CV: {cv_scores.mean():.4f} (¬±{cv_scores.std()*2:.4f})\")\n",
        "    print(f\"üéØ Test Accuracy: {accuracy:.4f}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"üìà Test AUC: {auc_score:.4f}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"‚ö° F1-Score: {f1:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Feature importance analysis\n",
        "    if hasattr(model.estimators_[0], 'feature_importances_'):\n",
        "        feature_importance = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "            'feature': optimal_features,\n",
        "            'importance': model.estimators_[0].feature_importances_\n",
        "        }).sort_values('importance', ascending=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "        print(f\"\\nüèÜ Top 5 Features:\")\n",
        "        for i, row in feature_importance.head(5).iterrows():\n",
        "            print(f\"   {row['feature']}: {row['importance']:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Save complete model package\n",
        "    artifacts = {\n",
        "        'model': model,\n",
        "        'scaler': scaler,\n",
        "        'feature_names': optimal_features,\n",
        "        'feature_processor': UltraVoiceProcessor(),\n",
        "        'performance': {\n",
        "            'accuracy': accuracy,\n",
        "            'auc': auc_score,\n",
        "            'f1_score': f1,\n",
        "            'cv_mean': cv_scores.mean(),\n",
        "            'cv_std': cv_scores.std()\n",
        "        },\n",
        "        'metadata': {\n",
        "            'training_time': training_time,\n",
        "            'n_features': len(optimal_features),\n",
        "            'n_samples': len(X_train),\n",
        "            'feature_engineering': 'advanced'\n",
        "        }\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    joblib.dump(artifacts, 'ultra_parkinsons_model.pkl')\n",
        "    print(\"üíæ Ultra model package saved!\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return artifacts\n",
        "\n",
        "# 7. ULTRA-EFFICIENT PREDICTION\n",
        "def ultra_predict(audio_path, model_artifacts):\n",
        "    \"\"\"High-speed prediction with confidence\"\"\"\n",
        "    start_time = time.time()\n",
        "\n",
        "    processor = model_artifacts['feature_processor']\n",
        "    model = model_artifacts['model']\n",
        "    scaler = model_artifacts['scaler']\n",

        "# FIXED VOICE FEATURE EXTRACTION - GUARANTEED 20 FEATURES\n",
        "def extract_voice_features_20(audio_data, sr=22050):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Extract exactly 20 features - no exceptions!\"\"\"\n",
        "    features = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        # 1. PITCH ANALYSIS (6 features)\n",
        "        print(\"üéµ Analyzing pitch...\")\n",
        "        f0, voiced_flag, _ = librosa.pyin(audio_data, fmin=50, fmax=300, sr=sr, fill_na=0.0)\n",
        "        voiced_f0 = f0[voiced_flag & (f0 > 0)]\n",
        "\n",
        "        if len(voiced_f0) > 5:\n",
        "            features.extend([\n",
        "                np.mean(voiced_f0),      # Average pitch\n",
        "                np.std(voiced_f0),       # Pitch variability\n",
        "                np.median(voiced_f0),    # Median pitch\n",
        "                np.ptp(voiced_f0),       # Pitch range\n",
        "            ])\n",
        "\n",
        "            # JITTER (2 features)\n",
        "            jitter_abs = np.mean(np.abs(np.diff(voiced_f0)))\n",
        "            jitter_rel = jitter_abs / (np.mean(voiced_f0) + 1e-8)\n",
        "            features.extend([jitter_abs, jitter_rel])\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            # Use reasonable defaults if no pitch detected\n",
        "            features.extend([120.0, 25.0, 120.0, 80.0, 0.0001, 0.0008])\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. SHIMMER (2 features)\n",
        "        print(\"üìä Analyzing amplitude...\")\n",
        "        rms = librosa.feature.rms(y=audio_data, frame_length=2048, hop_length=512)[0]\n",
        "        if len(rms) > 5:\n",
        "            shimmer_abs = np.mean(np.abs(np.diff(rms)))\n",
        "            shimmer_rel = shimmer_abs / (np.mean(rms) + 1e-8)\n",
        "            features.extend([shimmer_abs, shimmer_rel])\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            features.extend([0.001, 0.02])\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. VOICE QUALITY (1 feature)\n",
        "        print(\"üé∂ Analyzing voice quality...\")\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            y_harmonic = librosa.effects.harmonic(audio_data, margin=8)\n",
        "            y_percussive = librosa.effects.percussive(audio_data, margin=8)\n",
        "            hnr = np.mean(y_harmonic**2) / (np.mean(y_percussive**2) + 1e-8)\n",
        "            features.append(min(hnr, 25.0))\n",
        "        except:\n",
        "            features.append(15.0)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 4. SPECTRAL FEATURES (11 features needed to reach 20 total)\n",
        "        print(\"üìà Analyzing spectral features...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # MFCCs (5 features)\n",
        "        mfccs = librosa.feature.mfcc(y=audio_data, sr=sr, n_mfcc=5)\n",
        "        for i in range(5):\n",
        "            features.append(np.mean(mfccs[i]))\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Spectral properties (6 features)\n",
        "        spectral_centroid = librosa.feature.spectral_centroid(y=audio_data, sr=sr)\n",
        "        features.append(np.mean(spectral_centroid))\n",
        "\n",
        "        spectral_rolloff = librosa.feature.spectral_rolloff(y=audio_data, sr=sr)\n",
        "        features.append(np.mean(spectral_rolloff))\n",
        "\n",
        "        spectral_bandwidth = librosa.feature.spectral_bandwidth(y=audio_data, sr=sr)\n",
        "        features.append(np.mean(spectral_bandwidth))\n",
        "\n",
        "        zero_crossing = librosa.feature.zero_crossing_rate(audio_data)\n",
        "        features.append(np.mean(zero_crossing))\n",
        "\n",
        "        spectral_contrast = librosa.feature.spectral_contrast(y=audio_data, sr=sr)\n",
        "        features.append(np.mean(spectral_contrast))\n",
        "\n",
        "        spectral_flatness = librosa.feature.spectral_flatness(y=audio_data)\n",
        "        features.append(np.mean(spectral_flatness))\n",
        "\n",
        "        # FORCE 20 FEATURES EXACTLY\n",
        "        print(f\"üìä Extracted {len(features)} features\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # If we have less than 20, add zeros\n",
        "        while len(features) < 20:\n",
        "            features.append(0.0)\n",
        "            print(f\"‚ûï Added placeholder to reach 20 features\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # If we have more than 20, trim to 20\n",
        "        features = features[:20]\n",
        "\n",
        "        print(f\"‚úÖ Final feature count: {len(features)}\")\n",
        "        return np.array(features, dtype=np.float32)\n",
        "\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"‚ùå Feature extraction error: {e}\")\n",
        "        # Return exactly 20 zeros on error\n",
